JOHANNESBURG - An historic agreement has been concluded which will see thousands of gold miners compensated for contracting silicosis, or tuberculosis. It’s the first class action settlement of its kind in South Africa and affects miners who worked at several mines from 1965, until now. READ: Study identifies TB test that's cheaper, quicker and more accurate Compensation will be paid to ill workers or their dependents. The amount concerned has not been revealed, but Reuters reports companies have already set aside R5-billion. The High Court in Johannesburg still has to approve the agreement. eNCA